# **Resume Analyzer**

**📅 Project Start Date:** May 13, 2025
**🛠 Programming Language:** Python 3

## 🔧 Requirements

* Only **PDF** documents are supported
* Only **German**-language PDFs are currently supported
* **Python 3** must be installed
* A **virtual environment** is strongly recommended

---

## 📦 Required Python Libraries

Install the following libraries using `pip` inside your virtual environment:

```bash
pip install pdfplumber
pip install pyqt6
pip install spacy
```

Download the necessary spaCy language models:

# German language model
python -m spacy download de_dep_news_trf

# English language model (optional, for future use)
python -m spacy download en_core_web_trf
```

---

## 🚀 Installation Guide

1. Download and install the latest version of Python from
   [https://www.python.org](https://www.python.org)
2. Set up a virtual environment on your system:

   ```bash
   python -m venv venv
   source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
   ```
3. Clone the repository:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/Agramm18/resumee_analyzer.git
   cd resumee_analyzer
   ```

---

## 🧱 Architecture Overview

```
GUI (PyQt6)
│
├── Input: Job advertisement text + PDF resume (drag & drop)
│
↓
Internal API Layer
│
├── Routes data from GUI to core modules
│
↓
PDF Reader (pdfplumber)
│
├── Extracts text from uploaded resume PDF
│
↓
Resume NLP Processor (spaCy)
│
├── Analyzes resume content: skills, experience, education, languages
│
↓
Job Ad NLP Processor (spaCy)
│
├── Analyzes job ad text: keywords, requirements
│
↓
AI Matching Engine (later: numpy, scikit-learn)
├── Compares both data sources
└── Calculates a matching score
```

---

## 🧪 How to Use

1. Paste the job advertisement text into the input field.
2. Drag & drop your resume PDF into the upload area.
3. The AI analyzes both inputs and calculates a **matching score**.
4. View your **match result** to assess your fit for the job.

---

## ⚙️ How the Matching Score is Calculated

The score is computed based on content alignment between your resume and the job ad:

### 🔍 From Resume:

* Programming and technical skills
* Language proficiencies
* Work experience
* Academic qualifications (school/university degrees)
* Hard and soft skills
* Portfolio or project experience

### 📋 From Job Advertisement:

* Explicitly required qualifications, skills, and experience